							<h3>Peer Review Process</h3>
							<p><p style="margin-bottom: 0in;" lang="en-US" align="JUSTIFY">The peer-review assessment process begins by sending a copy of the material to an expert or privileged actor in the field, so that – independently- peers could exposed their concepts regarding the appropriateness of publishing the work, considering the following criteria: quality or academic level, originality, contribution to knowledge and teaching, clarity of presentation, clarity of writing and literature, interest and topicality.</p><p> </p><!--EndFragment--></p>
